===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|能|火|c1=p|c2=s|t2=fire|ls=psc}}.

This character originally represented an onomatopoetic word ({{zh-l|熊熊|''(of flame)'' raging}}). Later its phonetic compound {{och-l|能}}, the character for the Old Chinese word "bear", was borrowed for another word. This character thus began to represent the word "bear" instead.

